  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What are the best mobile apps for learning to program?",
  "response": "There are several excellent mobile apps available for learning programming, catering to a range of skill levels and programming languages. Here are some of the best apps:\n\n1. **SoloLearn**: This app offers a variety of programming courses in languages including Python, JavaScript, Java, C++, and more. It features a community-driven environment for Q&A and code sharing.\n\n2. **Programming Hub**: With a user-friendly interface, Programming Hub provides coding courses in multiple languages. It includes interactive examples, quizzes, and a supportive community.\n\n3. **Grasshopper**: Developed by Google, Grasshopper is a free app designed to teach JavaScript through fun, interactive puzzles and challenges aimed at beginners.\n\n4. **Mimo**: Mimo allows users to learn various programming languages and technologies like HTML, CSS, JavaScript, Python, SQL, and more through bite-sized lessons and hands-on exercises.\n\n5. **Codecademy Go**: This companion app to Codecademy offers access to coding exercises and quizzes, allowing learners to practice what they've learned in Codecademy\u2019s online courses.\n\n6. **Khan Academy**: Known for its vast array of educational content, Khan Academy also offers programming courses, particularly in JavaScript and web development, complemented by interactive coding challenges.\n\n7. **Swift Playgrounds**: Designed for learning Swift, Apple's programming language for iOS development, this app combines fun puzzles and challenges to teach coding in an engaging way.\n\n8. **Enki**: Enki is a learning platform that offers a variety of coding topics, with lessons designed as daily bite-sized content to help you build your programming skills regularly.\n\n9. **Py**: Py offers interactive courses on various programming languages, including Python and JavaScript. It includes quizzes and coding challenges to reinforce learning.\n\n10. **CodeCombat**: This app makes learning coding fun by turning it into a game where users write code to control their character and navigate through challenges.\n\nThese apps can help you start your programming journey, whether you're a complete beginner or looking to enhance your skills. It\u2019s beneficial to try a few different apps to see which one aligns best with your learning style.",
